      "message": "For what it\u0027s worth, this pattern here was me trying to create a dividing line between our inputs and the results of SkBitmapController\u0027s decisions, overwriting matrix/quality to make it difficult to impossible to accidentally use the original inputs instead of the output of SkBitmapController.  It would be a bug if we used paintQuality past the call to RequestBitmap(), right?  But annoyingly it\u0027s still in scope, so there\u0027s a risk we might accidentally pick it up again.  I found overwriting it to be the easiest way to indicate that, though maybe we can introduce some helper functions or just artificial {} scopes to make it really impossible.",
